The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Good Morning
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Good Morning
      Hello It's Friday , June 6 , 2008                      
	Whats on    Emergency services like hospitals, blood banks, medicine shops, and hearses will be outside the purview of the bandh.    State and central government departments will be open but employees may not turn up.    High Court and other subordinate city courts will remain open.    State and private buses will ply.     Autorickshaws will ply.    Taxi associations said     here is no bar on taxis plying but services may be insufficient.     Cars carrying passengers to ceremonial houses will be allowed to ply.    Metro Railway authorities said trains will ply according to schedule. But the frequency may be regulated depending upon the bandh situation and number of passengers.     All long-distance and suburban trains of both Eastern and South-Eastern railways will run on schedule, provided there is no disruption on tracks.    All 19 markets run by the Calcutta Municipal Corporation will be officially open but many shop-owners are expected to keep their establishments closed.    All airlines will operate as per schedule. Emergency numbers: Air India: 18001801407. Jet Airways: 39893333. Kingfisher Airlines: 18002093030/18001800101.    ndiGo: 18001803838. Deccan airlines: 18004257008.    IT services will remain outside the purview of the bandh.    
	Whats off    Zee Next Anandalok Jalsa, which was scheduled to be held at Nazrul Mancha.     Panel discussion on World Day against Child Labour at American Center.    Universities, colleges and other educational institutions. All scheduled examinations have been postponed.    Most malls and art galleries will be closed during the day.                                                                                                                                                                 
